---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof for Travel Agents — Client Reviews That Book More Trips | SocialProof" description="Travel agents: collect client testimonials that prove your expertise and personal touch. Win the trust of travelers who could book direct but choose you for a reason.">
  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for Travel Agents
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Travelers can book online themselves. When they choose a travel agent, they're paying for expertise, peace of mind, and someone to call when things go sideways. Your client testimonials need to prove that's what you deliver — and prove it before they decide you're worth the consultation.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Why testimonials are the key differentiator for travel agents</h2>
      <p>Booking.com and Expedia have convenience. You have relationships, expertise, and personal care. The prospect's question is: "Is this agent actually better than doing it myself?" Client testimonials that describe real moments — the upgrade you arranged, the crisis you solved, the trip you planned that exceeded expectations — answer that question definitively.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Testimonial moments that convert travel clients</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Problem solving:</strong> "Our flight was cancelled. She had us rerouted with hotel accommodations within 2 hours. Worth every penny."</li>
        <li><strong>Local knowledge:</strong> "She knew which room category got the best view. Those details made the trip."</li>
        <li><strong>Complex itineraries:</strong> "We wanted 4 countries in 10 days with two kids. She made it look effortless."</li>
        <li><strong>Value:</strong> "She found upgrades and deals I never could have found booking myself. Actually saved us money."</li>
        <li><strong>Relationship:</strong> "We've booked 7 trips with her. She knows our travel style better than we do."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">How to build a testimonial collection habit</h2>
      <p>Send your SocialProof collection link 3-5 days after your clients return from their trip — when the memories are vivid but they're back to daily life and ready to reflect. A simple text message with "Hope the trip was everything you dreamed! Would you mind sharing a quick review?" converts extremely well for travel agents.</p>

      <div style="background:#f0f7ff;border-radius:12px;padding:2rem;margin-top:3rem;text-align:center;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.8rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Prove your value with client testimonials</h2>
        <p style="color:#555;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Free forever for 1 active widget. No credit card required.</p>
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" style="background:#2563eb;color:white;padding:0.9rem 2rem;border-radius:8px;text-decoration:none;font-weight:700;font-size:1.1rem;">Get Started Free</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
